TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$a=random(-3,-1,1);
$b=random(3,6,1);
$c=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);

BEGIN_TEXT

$PAR
Using disks or washers, find the volume of the solid obtained by rotating the region bounded by the curves \(y=1/x,\) \(y=0,\) \(x=1,\) and \(x=$b\) about the line \(y=-1.\)

$PAR
Volume = \{ans_rule(30)\}

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp("pi*((-1/$b+2*ln($b))-(-1))"));

